title: Piecewise smooth maps on simplicial complices
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Let $$M$$ be a simplicial complex. A map $$f\colon C(M) \to \R$$ is called //piecewise smooth// if its restriction to every simplex of $$M$$ is smooth.

Piecewise smooth maps are automatically continuous.